or example, between 7 (0111) and 8 (1000). The highest number x such that the AND of [x, n] is zero\n# is the highest power of 2 less than or equal to n, minus one.\n```\n\nThis solution efficiently finds the maximum integer `x` such that the bitwise AND of all numbers in the range `[x, n]` is zero by leveraging the properties of powers of two. The time complexity is O(log n) due to the loop that finds the highest power of two less than or equal to `n`.", "estimated_date": 1713657600000}